content.description:
On boulder left of Practology. Stand start matched on obvious rail, go straight up the overhanging bulge using slopers and tension until a rail about 3-4 feet from the top.  

  This may be considerably easier when it's cold, I'll have to go back and see.  

  I escaped left into the dihedral from that rail, but a direct finish looks feasible and should be pretty fun. 

  A sit start may add a couple of moves, but I haven't explored it yet.
content.protection: pads, spotters. pad the tree directly under the problem, and maybe some more all down the hill to the sidewalk. a little exciting
content.location: Left boulder, stand start on right angled rail directly behind tree.

content.description: Continue up the arete to the undercling. After the undercling, the height becomes heady, but keep going!
content.protection: 2 pads recommended and a good spotter. I have never fallen on the tree, but it is a possibility.
content.location: Sit start on the tree located almost right between the 2 boulders. This is the most obvious line starting on the left arete of the right boulder. There is a stand start option, standing on the tree to get the undercling as a starting hold.

content.description: This is another road side boulder. As urban as it gets, 2 boulders sandwiched between 2 billboards. Rock Quality is excellent.   Most of the lines are believed to not be sent
